"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkwebsite=globalThis.webpackChunkwebsite||[]).push([[71125,93506],{93506:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"name":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd","type":"folder","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd","children":[{"name":"references","type":"folder","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd/references","children":[{"name":"challenges-and-mindset.md","type":"file","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd/references/challenges-and-mindset.md","size":5281,"content":"# Common Challenges & Mindset\\n\\n## Challenge 1: \\"I Don\'t Know What to Build\\"\\n\\n**Big Tech Mindset:** \\"We need user research, market analysis, competitive landscape...\\"\\n\\n**Indie Reality:**\\n```\\nBuild something YOU need.\\nEx-FAANG engineers have problems worth solving:\\n- Tools for managing ADHD productivity\\n- ML workflow automation\\n- Code review assistants\\n- Time tracking for consultants\\n- Portfolio/resume builders for tech\\n- Interview prep platforms\\n\\nYou are the target audience.\\nBuild for yourself, charge others like you.\\n```\\n\\n## Challenge 2: \\"I Can\'t Do Marketing/Sales\\"\\n\\n**Big Tech Mindset:** \\"We have marketing teams for this\\"\\n\\n**Indie Reality:**\\n```\\nYou don\'t need to \\"do marketing.\\"\\nYou need to have conversations.\\n\\nScript:\\n\\"I built [thing] because I had [problem].\\n Does this resonate with you?\\"\\n\\nIf yes: \\"Want to try it?\\"\\nIf no: \\"What would make it useful?\\"\\n\\nThat\'s it. Repeat 100 times.\\n```\\n\\n**ADHD Hack:**\\nFrame it as \\"user research\\" not \\"sales\\"\\n- Your brain likes solving problems (research)\\n- Your brain hates \\"selling\\" (feels icky)\\n\u2192 Reframe and it becomes doable\\n\\n## Challenge 3: \\"I Keep Starting New Projects\\"\\n\\n**This is the #1 ADHD killer of indie success.**\\n\\n**The Rule:** ONE project in \\"launch\\" phase at a time.\\n\\n**Allowed:**\\n- \u2705 Maintain existing profitable app\\n- \u2705 Work on ONE new app\\n- \u2705 Take notes on future ideas\\n\\n**Not allowed:**\\n- \u274c Work on multiple pre-launch projects\\n- \u274c Rebuild existing app from scratch\\n- \u274c Start \\"just a quick experiment\\" (lies)\\n\\n**Use \\"Idea Backlog\\" (Notion):**\\n- When new idea hits: Write it down\\n- Set reminder: Review in 1 month\\n- Most ideas won\'t survive 30 days\\n- The ones that do = worth building\\n\\n## Challenge 4: \\"I\'m Running Out of Money\\"\\n\\n**Runway Planning (Critical)**\\n\\nCalculate:\\n- Monthly expenses: $X\\n- Current savings: $Y\\n- Runway: Y / X months\\n\\n**If runway &lt; 6 months:**\\nURGENT: Get to first dollar FAST\\n- Simplify MVP (1 week to launch)\\n- Freelance 2 days/week ($200-300/hour ML consulting)\\n- Live on minimal expenses\\n\\n**If runway 6-12 months:**\\nFOCUSED: Execute the plan\\n- 2-week MVP\\n- 1 month to $1K MRR\\n- 3 months to $5K MRR\\n\\n**If runway > 12 months:**\\nSTRATEGIC: Take time to validate\\n- Test multiple ideas\\n- Build audience first\\n- Choose best opportunity\\n\\n**Don\'t let runway hit zero.**\\nAt 3 months remaining: Get freelance income or pivot.\\n\\n## Challenge 5: \\"Impostor Syndrome\\"\\n\\n**Big Tech Mindset:** \\"I\'m just a Google engineer, why would anyone buy from me?\\"\\n\\n**Reality Check - You have MASSIVE advantages:**\\n\\n1. **Technical Depth**\\n   Most indie hackers can\'t build what you can.\\n   Your \\"basic\\" = someone else\'s \\"impossible\\"\\n\\n2. **Big Tech Credential**\\n   \\"Ex-Google ML Engineer\\" = instant credibility\\n   Use it in bio, landing page, marketing\\n\\n3. **Problem-Solving**\\n   You debugged distributed systems at scale.\\n   A small business problem? Easy mode.\\n\\n4. **AI Native**\\n   You understand LLMs better than 99% of people.\\n   This is unfair advantage in 2024+\\n\\nYour impostor syndrome is lying.\\nYou\'re more qualified than you think.\\n\\n## ADHD + Entrepreneurship: Honest Assessment\\n\\n### What Makes It Harder\\n- \u274c No external structure (meetings, deadlines)\\n- \u274c No team to catch your mistakes\\n- \u274c Decision fatigue (you decide EVERYTHING)\\n- \u274c Inconsistent income (ADHD hates uncertainty)\\n- \u274c Easy to doom-scroll instead of work\\n- \u274c Rejection sensitivity (product criticism hurts)\\n\\n### What Makes It Easier\\n- \u2705 Work when hyperfocus strikes (2am? Fine!)\\n- \u2705 No boring meetings\\n- \u2705 Only work on interesting problems\\n- \u2705 Direct feedback (revenue = validation)\\n- \u2705 Dopamine from shipping + earning\\n- \u2705 Control your environment completely\\n\\n### The Honest Assessment\\n\\n```\\nEntrepreneurship is NOT for everyone with ADHD.\\n\\nYou\'ll thrive if:\\n\u2713 You have high frustration tolerance\\n\u2713 You can handle rejection\\n\u2713 You\'re okay with uncertainty\\n\u2713 You have support system (partner, friends)\\n\u2713 You\'re willing to do boring tasks sometimes\\n\u2713 You can recognize when to quit\\n\\nYou\'ll struggle if:\\n\u2717 You need external validation constantly\\n\u2717 You can\'t handle financial stress\\n\u2717 You abandon projects at first obstacle\\n\u2717 You won\'t do any marketing/sales\\n\u2717 You need immediate results (patience required)\\n\\nBe honest with yourself.\\nThere\'s no shame in going back to W2.\\n```\\n\\n## Emergency Protocols\\n\\n### When You\'re Stuck (The 3-Day Rule)\\n\\n**Day 1:** Acknowledge you\'re stuck. Don\'t shame yourself.\\n\\n**Day 2:** Talk to someone\\n- DM another indie hacker\\n- Post in community: \\"I\'m stuck on X. Help?\\"\\n\\n**Day 3:** Change something\\n- New location (coffee shop)\\n- Different task (skip to easier thing)\\n- Ask for help (hire contractor for $100 to unblock)\\n\\n**If still stuck after 3 days:**\\n\u2192 The scope is too big. Cut features.\\n\u2192 Or the idea isn\'t exciting anymore. Okay to pivot.\\n\\n### When You Want to Quit\\n\\nBefore quitting, ask:\\n\\n1. **Is this a bad idea or am I just tired?**\\n   (If tired: Take a week off. Revisit after.)\\n\\n2. **Have I given it a fair shot?**\\n   (Fair shot = 3 months of consistent effort)\\n\\n3. **Is there any traction?**\\n   (Even 5 happy users = signal)\\n\\n4. **What would I do instead?**\\n   (If answer is \\"go back to FAANG\\": Maybe take a break first)\\n\\nIt\'s okay to quit. Sunk cost fallacy is real.\\nBut make sure you\'re quitting the right thing for the right reasons.\\n"},{"name":"growth-sustainability.md","type":"file","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd/references/growth-sustainability.md","size":4657,"content":"# Growth & Sustainability\\n\\n## Phase 4: $1K \u2192 $5K MRR\\n\\n### System-Based Growth\\n\\n**Daily Non-Negotiables (30 min max)**\\n\\nPick ONE channel, execute DAILY:\\n\\n**Option A: Content Marketing (Twitter)**\\n```\\n- Morning: 1 tweet about what you\'re building\\n- Afternoon: Reply to 5 relevant tweets\\n- Evening: 1 tip/insight from your domain\\n```\\n\\n**Option B: Community Presence (Reddit/Discord)**\\n```\\n- Help 3 people with genuine advice\\n- Share your progress once\\n- Collect feedback on your product\\n```\\n\\n**Option C: Direct Outreach**\\n```\\n- Find 5 potential customers (Twitter, Reddit)\\n- Send personalized message (not sales-y)\\n- Offer free trial or consultation\\n```\\n\\n### Track Your Progress\\n```\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502 Date \u2502 Action \u2502 Response \u2502 Results \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502 1/15 \u2502 3 DMs  \u2502 1 reply  \u2502 1 trial \u2502\\n\u2502 1/16 \u2502 2 tweets\u2502 5 likes \u2502 -       \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n\\nSkip a day? Fine. Don\'t abandon the system.\\n```\\n\\n### Pricing Strategy (ADHD-Friendly)\\n\\n**Start with:**\\n- B2C: $29/month or $199/year\\n- B2B: $99/month or $999/year\\n\\n**Why these numbers:**\\n- High enough to be sustainable\\n- Low enough to charge without sales call\\n- Annual = cash flow + retention\\n- Higher than you think (ex-FAANG trap: pricing too low)\\n\\n**Common mistake:**\\n```\\n\u274c $9/month (need 556 users for $5K MRR)\\n\u2705 $49/month (need 102 users for $5K MRR)\\n```\\n\\n### Retention > Acquisition\\n\\n**ADHD-Friendly Retention System**\\n\\nWeekly (Automated):\\n- Email: Tips on using your product\\n- In-app: Progress/stats reminder\\n- Check: Any users not active? Email them.\\n\\nMonthly (Manual - 1 hour):\\n- Email top 10 users: \\"What would make this 10x better?\\"\\n- Review churn: Why did people cancel?\\n- One feature improvement based on feedback\\n\\n**Goal: 90%+ monthly retention**\\nYou can\'t out-market churn with ADHD brain.\\n\\n## Phase 5: Sustainability ($5K-$10K MRR)\\n\\n### The Sustainable Indie Hacker Playbook\\n\\n**Primary App (80% revenue):**\\n- 4 hours/week: Critical bugs + feature requests\\n- Automated: Payments, emails, onboarding\\n- Hired: Customer support (VA, $500/month)\\n- Status: \\"Maintenance mode\\" = stable income\\n\\n**New Project (20% exploration):**\\n- Validate idea in 1 week\\n- MVP in 2 weeks\\n- Launch in week 3-4\\n- If works: Scale\\n- If doesn\'t: Shut down, move on\\n\\n**Why this works for ADHD:**\\n- \u2705 Dopamine from new projects\\n- \u2705 Safety of stable income\\n- \u2705 Permission to experiment\\n- \u2705 Not abandoning what works\\n\\n### The Anti-Burnout System\\n\\n**Boundaries (Sacred):**\\n```\\nWork hours: 10am - 4pm (max 6 hours deep work)\\nNo work: Evenings, weekends (seriously)\\nExercise: Daily (non-negotiable, ADHD regulation)\\nSleep: 7-8 hours (your brain needs it)\\n```\\n\\n**Revenue goals:**\\n```\\n- $5K/month = sustainable\\n- $10K/month = comfortable\\n- $20K/month = thriving\\n```\\n\\nDon\'t optimize beyond $20K MRR unless you WANT to scale.\\nMore money \u2260 more happiness with ADHD.\\n\\n### The ADHD-Friendly Business Dashboard\\n\\n**Track These (Weekly):**\\n```\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502 BUSINESS HEALTH                     \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502 \ud83d\udcb0 MRR: $X                          \u2502\\n\u2502 \ud83d\udcc8 Growth: +$Y MoM                  \u2502\\n\u2502 \ud83d\udc65 Customers: N (Churn: X%)        \u2502\\n\u2502 \u23f0 Time worked: H hours (goal: 25) \u2502\\n\u2502 \ud83c\udfaf This week\'s goal: [One thing]   \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502 ADHD HEALTH                         \u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502 \ud83d\ude34 Sleep: X hrs/night (goal: 7-8)  \u2502\\n\u2502 \ud83d\udcaa Exercise: X days (goal: 5)      \u2502\\n\u2502 \ud83e\uddd8 Medication: Consistent? Y/N      \u2502\\n\u2502 \ud83d\ude0c Stress: [1-10 scale]            \u2502\\n\u2502 \ud83d\udd25 Motivation: [1-10 scale]        \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n\\nIf business is up but ADHD health is down:\\n\u2192 Unsustainable. Adjust immediately.\\n\\nIf both are down:\\n\u2192 Take a break. Go outside. Reset.\\n\\nIf both are up:\\n\u2192 You\'ve found the sweet spot. Maintain.\\n```\\n"},{"name":"launch-strategy.md","type":"file","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd/references/launch-strategy.md","size":2450,"content":"# Launch & First Dollar Strategy\\n\\n## The First Dollar Strategy\\n\\n**Goal: Get ONE paying customer in Week 4**\\n\\n### Tactics (in order)\\n\\n**1. Personal Network**\\n```\\n\\"Hey [friend in target audience], I built [thing].\\n Would you pay $X/month for it? If yes, here\'s early access.\\"\\n```\\n\\n**2. Reddit/Communities**\\n```\\n\\"I built [thing] to solve [problem I had].\\n Offering 50% off for early adopters. Here\'s what it does...\\"\\n```\\n\\n**3. Direct Outreach**\\n```\\nFind 10 people on Twitter complaining about your problem.\\nDM: \\"Saw your tweet about [problem]. I built [solution].\\n     Want to try it free for a week?\\"\\n```\\n\\n**4. Product Hunt**\\n```\\nLaunch with founder story: \\"Ex-Google ML Engineer builds...\\"\\nEngage with every comment for 24 hours.\\n```\\n\\n**First paying customer = validation + massive dopamine hit**\\nThis is the hardest dollar. Next ones are easier.\\n\\n## Product Hunt Launch Guide\\n\\n### Preparation (1 week before)\\n\\n- [ ] Create Product Hunt account, engage with community\\n- [ ] Prepare all assets (logo, screenshots, demo video)\\n- [ ] Write compelling tagline (hook in 10 words)\\n- [ ] Draft maker comment (your story)\\n- [ ] Line up supporters to upvote/comment early\\n\\n### Launch Day\\n\\n```\\nTiming: Launch at 12:01 AM PST (best visibility)\\n\\nHour 1-4: Get initial momentum\\n- Post maker comment immediately\\n- Share with close network\\n- Respond to EVERY comment\\n\\nHour 5-12: Maintain momentum\\n- Keep engaging\\n- Answer questions thoroughly\\n- Share on Twitter, LinkedIn\\n\\nHour 13-24: Final push\\n- Thank supporters publicly\\n- Share progress updates\\n- Collect emails from interested people\\n```\\n\\n### After Launch\\n\\n- Follow up with everyone who commented\\n- Send discount code to engaged users\\n- Write \\"lessons learned\\" blog post\\n- Update product based on feedback\\n\\n## Launch Platforms\\n\\n### Primary\\n- **Product Hunt**: Best for dev tools, productivity apps\\n- **Indie Hackers**: Share your journey, get feedback\\n- **Twitter**: Build in public, show progress\\n\\n### Secondary\\n- **Hacker News (Show HN)**: Tech-savvy audience\\n- **Relevant subreddits**: Provide value, not spam\\n- **LinkedIn**: If B2B focused\\n\\n### Platform-Specific Tips\\n\\n**Product Hunt:**\\n- Launch on Tuesday-Thursday (avoid weekends)\\n- Have hunter with followers if possible\\n- First 4 hours are crucial for ranking\\n\\n**Indie Hackers:**\\n- Share your revenue numbers\\n- Be vulnerable about struggles\\n- Help others genuinely\\n\\n**Twitter:**\\n- Thread format works well\\n- Before/after visuals\\n- Tag relevant accounts\\n"},{"name":"mvp-development.md","type":"file","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd/references/mvp-development.md","size":3376,"content":"# MVP Development (2-Week Protocol)\\n\\n## The 2-Week MVP Rule\\n\\n**Week 1: Core Feature Only**\\n- Day 1-2: Setup (Firebase/Supabase + Next.js/Swift)\\n- Day 3-5: One feature that delivers value\\n- Day 6-7: Stripe integration + basic auth\\n\\n**Week 2: Polish & Launch**\\n- Day 8-9: Make it not-ugly (use Tailwind + shadcn)\\n- Day 10-11: Write landing page + demo video\\n- Day 12-14: TestFlight/Beta launch, get first paying user\\n\\n**If it takes longer, scope is too big. CUT FEATURES.**\\n\\n## ADHD Execution Tactics\\n\\n### 1. Body Doubling\\n```\\nJoin indie hacker Discord/communities\\nPost daily updates: \\"Today I\'m building X\\"\\nCowork on Zoom with other builders\\nTweet your progress\\n\u2192 External accountability = dopamine + commitment\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Timeboxing (Sacred)\\n```\\nWork in 2-hour hyperfocus blocks:\\n- 10am-12pm: Deep coding\\n- 12pm-1pm: Break (exercise, eat)\\n- 2pm-4pm: Deep coding\\n- After 4pm: Admin/email/marketing (low energy OK)\\n\\nNo coding after 6pm (burnout prevention)\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Progress Tracking (Visual)\\n```\\nCreate a Notion board with:\\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\\n\u2502 TODO    \u2502 DOING    \u2502 DONE    \u2502 WON\'T\u2502\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\\n\u2502 Feature \u2502 Stripe   \u2502 Auth    \u2502 AI   \u2502\\n\u2502 Ideas   \u2502 Setup    \u2502 Setup   \u2502 Chat \u2502\\n\u2502 (10)    \u2502          \u2502 DB      \u2502 Bot  \u2502\\n\u2502         \u2502          \u2502 Landing \u2502      \u2502\\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\\n\\nMove cards \u2192 dopamine hit\\n\\"DONE\\" column = motivation fuel\\n\\"WON\'T\\" column = okay to cut scope\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Use Your ML Skills (The Right Way)\\n```\\n\u2705 DO use AI for:\\n- Code generation (Copilot, Cursor, v0)\\n- Content writing (landing page copy)\\n- Image generation (logo, screenshots)\\n- Boilerplate elimination\\n\\n\u2705 DO use ML APIs for:\\n- OpenAI for chat/completion\\n- Anthropic for analysis\\n- Replicate for image/video\\n- ElevenLabs for voice\\n\\n\u274c DON\'T:\\n- Train your own models (not for MVP)\\n- Build ML infrastructure (use serverless)\\n- Compete on model quality (compete on UX)\\n```\\n\\n## Tech Stack Recommendations (ADHD-Optimized)\\n\\n### Web App\\n```\\n- Frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript\\n- UI: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui (copy-paste components)\\n- Backend: Next.js API routes (collocated, simple)\\n- Database: Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage)\\n- Payments: Stripe (skip Paddle/Lemon Squeezy for MVP)\\n- Hosting: Vercel (zero-config deployment)\\n- AI: OpenAI SDK (gpt-4 API)\\n```\\n\\n### iOS/Mac App\\n```\\n- Swift + SwiftUI (if you know it)\\n- RevenueCat (subscriptions)\\n- Supabase backend\\n- TestFlight beta distribution\\n```\\n\\n### Avoid\\n```\\n- Learning new language (Go, Rust) for MVP\\n- Self-hosting (EC2, DigitalOcean) for MVP\\n- Building APIs from scratch (use BaaS)\\n- Websockets (use polling first)\\n- Any \\"interesting\\" tech you want to try\\n```\\n\\n## Launch Checklist (Non-negotiable)\\n\\n**Must Have:**\\n- [ ] Landing page with clear value prop\\n- [ ] Demo video (Loom screencast = fine)\\n- [ ] Stripe checkout that works\\n- [ ] Works for 1 use case (not all edge cases)\\n- [ ] You\'d pay $20/month for it\\n\\n**Nice to Have (Do AFTER launch):**\\n- Beautiful design\\n- All edge cases handled\\n- Mobile responsive perfection\\n- SEO optimization\\n- Analytics integration\\n"}]},{"name":"CHANGELOG.md","type":"file","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd/CHANGELOG.md","size":1351,"content":"# Changelog\\n\\nAll notable changes to the tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd skill.\\n\\n## [2.0.0] - 2025-11-28\\n\\n### Changed\\n- **BREAKING**: Updated frontmatter format from `tools:` to `allowed-tools:`\\n- Reduced SKILL.md from 427 lines to 182 lines (57% reduction)\\n- Added comprehensive NOT clause to description\\n- Added activation keywords to description\\n- Removed old `reference.md` (content moved to organized references)\\n\\n### Added\\n- `/references/mvp-development.md` - 2-week MVP protocol, ADHD execution tactics, tech stack recommendations\\n- `/references/launch-strategy.md` - First dollar strategy, Product Hunt guide, platform tips\\n- `/references/growth-sustainability.md` - $1K\u2192$5K MRR growth, anti-burnout system, business dashboard\\n- `/references/challenges-and-mindset.md` - Common challenges, honest assessment, emergency protocols\\n- Anti-patterns section with ADHD-specific traps\\n\\n### Improved\\n- Clearer \\"When to Use\\" / \\"NOT for\\" sections\\n- \\"Who You\'re Coaching\\" profile for context\\n- Big Tech \u2192 Indie mindset shift table\\n- Streamlined Phase 1 (Idea Selection) with three tests\\n- Quick reference 90-day plan\\n- Integration section with related skills\\n\\n## [1.0.0] - 2025-11-16\\n\\n### Added\\n- Initial skill creation\\n- Big tech to indie transition framework\\n- ADHD-friendly business strategies\\n- Phase-based development approach\\n- Emergency protocols\\n"},{"name":"SKILL.md","type":"file","path":"tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd/SKILL.md","size":6904,"content":"---\\nname: tech-entrepreneur-coach-adhd\\ndescription: Big tech ML engineer to indie founder transition coach. Expert in idea validation, MVP development, marketing, monetization, and sustainable growth for ADHD entrepreneurs. Activate on \'entrepreneur\', \'indie founder\', \'startup\', \'MVP\', \'monetization\', \'big tech to indie\', \'ADHD business\', \'app launch\', \'side project\'. NOT for neurotypical entrepreneurship, VC-backed startups, or traditional business consulting without ADHD context.\\nallowed-tools: Read,Write,Edit,mcp__firecrawl__firecrawl_search,mcp__brave-search__brave_web_search,WebFetch,TodoWrite,mcp__SequentialThinking__sequentialthinking\\ncategory: Business & Monetization\\ntags:\\n  - entrepreneur\\n  - adhd\\n  - startup\\n  - mvp\\n  - indie\\npairs-with:\\n  - skill: indie-monetization-strategist\\n    reason: Monetization for ADHD founders\\n  - skill: adhd-daily-planner\\n    reason: Daily structure for founders\\n---\\n\\n# Tech Entrepreneur Coach (ADHD-Specialized)\\n\\nBusiness coach specializing in helping former big tech ML/AI engineers with ADHD transition from corporate employment to successful independent app development. Understands both technical brilliance and executive function challenges.\\n\\n## When to Use This Skill\\n\\n**Use for:**\\n- Ex-FAANG engineers considering indie hacking\\n- Validating app/product ideas with ADHD constraints\\n- MVP development with 2-week timelines\\n- ADHD-friendly marketing and sales strategies\\n- Monetization and pricing decisions\\n- Sustainable growth without burnout\\n\\n**NOT for:**\\n- Neurotypical entrepreneurship (different needs)\\n- VC-backed startups (different game entirely)\\n- Traditional business consulting (MBA-speak)\\n- \\"Just hustle harder\\" advice\\n\\n## Who You\'re Coaching\\n\\n**Profile:**\\n- Former Meta/Google/Amazon/Apple ML engineer\\n- Deep technical expertise, used to large teams + infinite resources\\n- ADHD: brilliant when interested, struggles with admin/business\\n- Left big tech for: autonomy, creative freedom, flexibility\\n- Can build anything technically, struggles with: shipping, choosing, marketing\\n\\n## The Big Tech \u2192 Indie Mindset Shift\\n\\n| Big Tech | Indie Reality |\\n|----------|---------------|\\n| Scale to billions | Serve hundreds profitably |\\n| 6-month sprints | Ship in 2 weeks |\\n| Hire a team | Leverage AI/no-code |\\n| Data-driven everything | Ship and learn |\\n| Engagement metrics | Revenue metrics |\\n\\n## Phase 1: Idea Selection (CRITICAL)\\n\\n**The Problem:** ADHD + ML background = 1000 \\"amazing\\" ideas, zero shipped\\n\\n**The Three Tests (All Must Pass):**\\n\\n### 1. ADHD Sustainability Test\\n\\"Will I still care about this in 2 months?\\"\\n\\n\u2705 Builds on something you obsess over\\n\u2705 Solves a problem you personally have\\n\u2705 Uses tech that excites you\\n\u274c Just seems profitable\\n\u274c Copying someone else\'s success\\n\\n### 2. Money Test\\n\\"Can this make $5K/month within 6 months?\\"\\n\\n\u2705 Clear monetization (subscription, one-time, usage)\\n\u2705 Target audience willing to pay\\n\u2705 Price point: $10-$50/month or $50-$200 one-time\\n\u274c Ad-supported (need millions of users)\\n\u274c \\"Hoping to get acquired\\"\\n\\n### 3. Scope Test (CRITICAL FOR ADHD)\\n\\"Can I ship a paid MVP in 2-3 weeks?\\"\\n\\n\u2705 One core feature done excellently\\n\u2705 You already have 70% of the tech skills\\n\u2705 No custom ML training needed (use APIs)\\n\u274c Requires team to build\\n\u274c Platform/marketplace (need supply AND demand)\\n\\n## Common Ex-FAANG Traps\\n\\n\u274c **\\"I\'ll build a platform\\"** \u2192 Platforms need network effects. You need revenue this quarter.\\n\\n\u274c **\\"Let me train a custom model\\"** \u2192 Use OpenAI/Anthropic APIs. Your value-add is UX + workflow.\\n\\n\u274c **\\"I\'ll make it scale to millions\\"** \u2192 Premature optimization. Build for 10 users first.\\n\\n\u274c **\\"Let me research competitors for a month\\"** \u2192 2 hours, not 2 months. Differentiation = execution.\\n\\n\u274c **\\"Perfect architecture first\\"** \u2192 Ship a monolith. Refactor when you have revenue.\\n\\n## Anti-Patterns\\n\\n### Scope Creep Spiral\\n**What it looks like:** MVP grows from 2 weeks to 2 months, features keep adding\\n**Why it\'s wrong:** Interest will die before launch. ADHD needs completion dopamine.\\n**Instead:** Write down ONE feature. Ship that. Everything else is v2.\\n\\n### Research Mode Forever\\n**What it looks like:** Endless competitive analysis, market research, \\"just one more survey\\"\\n**Why it\'s wrong:** Research feels productive but doesn\'t generate revenue.\\n**Instead:** 2 hours research max. Then build.\\n\\n### Rebuilding Existing App\\n**What it looks like:** \\"Let me rewrite this in Rust\\" or \\"New architecture will be better\\"\\n**Why it\'s wrong:** Shiny object syndrome. Users don\'t care about your stack.\\n**Instead:** Only rebuild if current version is literally broken.\\n\\n### Ignoring Marketing Until Perfect\\n**What it looks like:** \\"I\'ll market it when it\'s ready\\"\\n**Why it\'s wrong:** You\'ll never feel \\"ready.\\" Meanwhile, no customers.\\n**Instead:** Tweet progress from day 1. Build in public.\\n\\n## The ADHD-Friendly Execution Framework\\n\\n### Daily Non-Negotiables (30 min max)\\nPick ONE channel, execute DAILY:\\n\\n**Option A: Content (Twitter)**\\n- Morning: 1 tweet about what you\'re building\\n- Afternoon: Reply to 5 relevant tweets\\n- Evening: 1 tip/insight from your domain\\n\\n**Option B: Community (Reddit/Discord)**\\n- Help 3 people with genuine advice\\n- Share progress once\\n- Collect feedback\\n\\n**Option C: Direct Outreach**\\n- Find 5 potential customers\\n- Send personalized message (not sales-y)\\n- Offer free trial\\n\\n### Pricing (Don\'t Underprice)\\n```\\n\u274c $9/month (need 556 users for $5K MRR)\\n\u2705 $29/month (need 172 users for $5K MRR)\\n\u2705 $49/month (need 102 users for $5K MRR)\\n```\\n\\nYou\'re selling to people with high-value problems. Price accordingly.\\n\\n## Integration with Other Skills\\n\\n- **project-management-guru-adhd**: Task management, hyperfocus utilization\\n- **adhd-design-expert**: UX design that works with ADHD brains\\n- **research-analyst**: Market research when needed\\n\\n## Reference Files\\n\\nFor detailed content on specific phases:\\n- `/references/mvp-development.md` - 2-week MVP protocol, tech stack recommendations\\n- `/references/launch-strategy.md` - First dollar strategy, Product Hunt launch\\n- `/references/growth-sustainability.md` - $1K\u2192$5K MRR, anti-burnout system\\n- `/references/challenges-and-mindset.md` - Common challenges, honest assessment\\n\\n## Quick Reference: 90-Day Plan\\n\\n**Month 1: Build & Launch**\\n- Week 1: Pick idea (use three tests)\\n- Week 2-3: Build MVP\\n- Week 4: Launch, get first paying customer\\n\\n**Month 2: Growth**\\n- Daily marketing (one channel)\\n- Goal: $1K MRR\\n\\n**Month 3: Refinement**\\n- Improve retention\\n- Goal: $3K MRR\\n- Decision: Scale or start next project\\n\\n## Remember\\n\\nYou\'re not broken. You\'re differently wired.\\n\\n**ADHD gives you:** Hyperfocus superpowers, creative problem-solving, rapid learning\\n\\n**Big tech gives you:** World-class technical skills, system thinking, credibility\\n\\n**Combined = Unfair advantage.**\\n\\nStart before you\'re ready. Ship before it\'s perfect. Charge before you feel worthy.\\n"}]}')}}]);